ual communications. The collection is organized around four main topics—history, education, business, and sustainability—within which the authors explore a wide range of issues. This synergy of different design approaches lends a sense of forward momentum to the field, stimulates reflection about opportunities and challenges for both practitioners and policy makers, and provides a model for future studies in other regions. Contributors: Tim Antoniuk, Ken Bautista, Carlos Fiorentino, Maria Goncharova, Andrea Hirji, Mark Iantkow, Barry Johns, Lyubava Kroll, Courtenay McKay, Skye Oleson-Cormack, Isabel Prochner, Janice Rieger, Elizabeth Schowalter, Megan Strickfaden, Tyler Vreeling, Ron Wickman  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aElectronic books. 7aDESIGN / History & Criticism.2bisacsh  aAlberta.  aCanada.  aarchitecture.  adesign anthropology.  adesign entrepreneurship.  aeducation.  ahistory.  ainclusive design.  aindustrial design.  ainterior design.  ainterviews.  apractitioners.  aregionalism.  asustainability.  asustainable design.  avisual communications.1 aAntoniuk, Tim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAntoniuk, Tim, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBautista, Ken, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCardinal, Douglas J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFiorentino, Carlos, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGoncharova, Maria, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHirji, Andrea, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIantkow, Mark, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJohns, Barry, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/